<br>
As for the report, as has already been said, disappointing.<br>
<br>
I think it's great they may consider a change to our DA and our DDs.  They are the battle tools of our unique spec line, so of course we would like them to br useful.<br>
<br>
But as for defence, it's unfortunate that the replier both understood the problems with class changes, but doesn't get the specifics of a skald.<br>
<br>
He or she states that making changes to the defence of our class is a 'slippery slope'.  S/he is quite right.  If you increase the defence of one or several classes, one begins to slide down a long hill of having to change defence or offence for every other class.<br>
<br>
Unfortunately what s/he fails to see is that this has already happened, and that we are one of the &quot;other classes&quot; needing to be brought in line...not a new unique change that requires altering other classes.  The large increases to the defensive abilites of other classes have already taken place over the last year, and our point is not to start a new trend of this, but to be one of those classes brought into line to MEET those changes.<br>
<br>
We're at the bottom of the slippery slope, not the top. <p>Clapperoth Liefarg<br>
