<br>
You guys might wanna keep an eye on the Shaman report.   The devs mentioned in their that they would most likely be increasing the Shaman DA.   Between the Runie and any Shaman increases, the skald DA just got that much less unique.<br>
<br>
I was hoping to read this report and find a reason to re-activate my accounts....but none so far. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=berdoon>Berdoon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/10/03 7:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=655.topic&index=40>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Feedback from our 1.62 Skald Report</span><hr size=1> I keep searching for words to communicate my extreme disappointment in Mythic's attitude towards Skalds and keep coming up short.  To continually ignore a classes shortcomings then dangle a small carrot ( increased range on chants/dd's ) is what I would term as &quot;Used Car Salesmanship&quot;.  Tell them the bare minimum it will take to get them to by off on another subscription term.  I am leveling a <br>
Spiritmaster, Warrior and Savage(in grave danger of the nerf bat, they are way too much fun) that I totally enjoy playing.<br>
<br>
Each and every time I take my Skald out to rvr, I grow less content.  Each and every time I pve with him his defense to  offense ratio is a more glaring downside to playing him.  Mostly I use him to pl my buffbot that I use to pl my other toons that I am enjoying so much more.<br>
<br>
Mythic's lackadaisical attitude towards this class, and so many other Midgard classes, is appalling.  It seems that they want a two realm war and are slowly phasing out Midgard as it is has the least aesthetic appeal and will require the most work to actually fix.  How many people know a Midgard class that actually buys it's class specific RA other than Shamans with Ichor ( which I see less and less of played Shaman's in the frontier ).<br>
<br>
They &quot;balanced&quot; Hibernia and Albion and nerf Midgard's definitive damage dealer that is based upon the realms mythos.  From the feed back that I see the only &quot;balancing&quot; Midgard will see is fluff, nothing to give us a competitive edge like the class specific RA's you see in Albion and Hibernia nor the class defining upward tweaks that Albion and Hibernia have seen in the recent past.<br>
<br>
Bottom line, Housing is way more important than Midgard.<br>
<br>
Once I have another level 50 toon my Skald will be a forge monkey and a door repair bot.<br>
<br>
